title: About Game Grumps
body:
The reason I like Game Grumps is because they’re both funny but also can be serious.

A lot of people who watch their games get annoyed that they’re “not paying attention to the games” that they’re playing. 

But they actually are.

I watched their Detroit game play, and they actually picked up in the first 5 seconds of the game - not even exaggerating: go watch the few minutes of the first episode - that it was going to be a game about prejudice, whereas I picked it up way later. Which proves that they do pay attention to every detail that’s in the game, even if they’re joking around.

I like how they can joke around and still be serious about what they’re doing: to me it shows how professional they are at their job: aka, being both entertaining and funny (because it’s a game show), and serious about what they’re doing / working on at the same time.

So I mentioned Detroit, but also Kitty Love: in which they have their usual sense of humor, but by the last episode they completely understood the game and summarized it very well, proving once again they were paying very much attention to what they were watching & doing, even if they’re goofing around. 

-

And I’m not saying this just about game grumps: I’ve seen other people get hate for “acting stupid” or what-not, which is insulting. Other people being told “they’re not very serious people” when in fact they are.
